# Product Analytics & Staff Discount Audit

Build a deep-dive analytics system for **individual product performance** and **staff discount auditing**, using data already captured in `bill_items` and `bills`.

---

## Background & Data Inventory

We already have everything we need in the database — **no migrations required**:

| Table | Columns Available | What It Gives Us |
|-------|------------------|------------------|
| `bill_items` | `product_id`, `product_name`, `qty`, `unit_price`, `cost_price`, `discount`, `subtotal`, `is_loose` | Per-item revenue, cost, profit, discount amount |
| `bills` | `id`, `created_by`, `created_at`, `status`, `discount_total`, `mode`, `bill_number`, `total` | Who created the bill, when, and total discount |
| `users` | `id`, `name`, `role` | Staff identity for discount attribution |
| `eod_entries` | `product_id`, `qty_sold`, `unit_price`, `cost_price`, `entry_date` | EOD-based product sales (no discount tracking — EOD has no discount field) |

The existing [getTopProducts](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/backend/src/features/analytics/analytics.service.ts#L347-L454) already aggregates by `product_id` with discount fields. We extend this pattern for deep-dive and staff audit views.

